ld becomes 3; if it's called when env is unset, the field becomes 7 from the default. Since only the override It actually calls Parse, the default It will always see the zero value of 0, which matches the expected result. The env is unset during the default It's BeforeEach, so when Parse is called it should apply the default value of 7 and set the struct field accordingly. My test logic appears sound. Looking at the test file, I'm noticing some messiness—there's a saved variable I set up, calls to LookupEnv that don't actually use the returned value, and that no-op assignment to silence an unused warning. I should clean this up.","signature":"503277c1e7f6c339ad8833675f697417eb86cb32ab7d595a940b3012634418e7"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":46432,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":23387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"baa6dde1-23ca-41c0-9d12-35b70b784ba6","uuid":"8d6ac1c8-481a-40f5-b917-8086177094f3"}
